History of Present Illness (HPI): The patient has experienced feelings of hopelessness, lack of energy, and concentration issues since being diagnosed with depression in 1997. They also mentioned having disturbing thoughts triggered by interpersonal issues or media exposure. Recently, they have been feeling withdrawn and have had difficulty sleeping due to racing thoughts at night.
Medical and Psychiatric History: The patient has been diagnosed with depression and previously sought therapy but stopped due to feeling unchallenged. They believe therapy can be beneficial when there is a connection with the therapist.

Progress Evaluation: The patient has shown improvement in expressing emotions and recognizing their reactions in various situations. They appreciate having a non-judgmental space to discuss their feelings.
